Objective Oriented Programming (OOPs):
     OOPs is a just a style of programmin .
     Just a way to writing code that helps us write large ammounts of code easily.
     It helps us manage and and change large amounts of code.
     There are other ways as well as functional programming and procedural programming.

Pillars of OOPs:
    There are four main pillars of OOPs.
    1) Inheritance
    2) Polymorphism
    3)Abstraction
    4)Encapsulation

Classes and Objects:
     A class is a tamplate or design /map / idea/ blueprint/from
     which objects are crested.


